Class ProcessCanceledException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.intellij.openapi.progress.ProcessCanceledException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ControlFlowException, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationUtil.CannotRunReadActionException, DiffTooBigException, ServiceNotReadyException

    public class ProcessCanceledException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
implements ControlFlowException
    An exception indicating that the currently running operation was terminated and should finish as soon as possible. Normally this exception should not be caught, swallowed, logged or handled in any way. It should be rethrown so that the infrastructure could handle it correctly. This exception can happen during almost any IDE activity, e.g. any PSI query, ExtensionPointName.getExtensions(), AnAction.update(com.intellij.openapi.actionSystem.AnActionEvent), etc.

    See Also:
    ProgressIndicator.checkCanceled(), General Threading Rules, Serialized Form
